🔴 CRITICAL — 1
C-03 Gap-fill yield still on wrong iteration — WDT risk on multi-day backlog
File: scheduler.ino Line: ~1442
What: vTaskDelay(1ms) and esp_task_wdt_reset() are inside the if (q == sampleNo) branch which executes only on the final iteration. All 94 preceding interpolation iterations (the heavy ones — esp_random() ×4, snprintf ×6, SPIFFS.print() ×2 per gap) run with no yield and no WDT pet.
Why it crashes: A 95-slot gap-fill (one missed day) with SPIFFS writes takes ~500–800 ms solid. With the 120 s WDT and all tasks at priority 2, tempHum and windSpeed are starved during this window. On BSNL stations that lose signal for entire nights, a 2–3 day gap fill on wakeup will WDT-reset mid-write, leaving a corrupt partial record in the daily log that future gap-detection misreads.
Fix:
cppfor (int q = last_sampleNo + 1; q <= sampleNo; q++) {
  esp_task_wdt_reset();               // ADD at top of loop body
  vTaskDelay(1 / portTICK_PERIOD_MS); // ADD at top of loop body
  // ... existing snprintf / interpolation / file.print work ...
}

