🟠 HIGH — 2 new findings
R-01 Torn time read in FTP scheduled-slot check
File: gprs.ino Lines: ~2071–2073
What: scheduled_slot and morning_cleanup read current_hour and current_min as two separate unprotected statements. rtcRead runs on Core 1 and writes these every second.
Why it matters: At 02:59:59 → 03:00:00, current_hour can be read as 2 while current_min is already 0, making 2 % 3 != 0 → scheduled_slot = false. The 3 AM FTP backlog push is silently skipped. Happens once per scheduled boundary per day — on a field unit with 6 hours of backlog, this means delayed delivery. Fix: snapshot both into locals under portENTER_CRITICAL(&rtcTimeMux) before evaluating.
R-02 SPIFFS.exists() outside fsMutex before SPIFFS.open() inside
File: gprs.ino Line: ~895, and multiple other sites
What: SPIFFS.exists(temp_file) is called outside fsMutex; if the prune loop (also holding fsMutex) deletes that file between the exists() returning true and the open() call, open() returns a null handle. The null handle is checked and skipped correctly, but the outgoing record for that slot is silently dropped — the data is lost without queuing to unsent.
Fix: Remove the SPIFFS.exists() guard entirely; take fsMutex, open directly, check the handle, release.

