File: AIO9_5.0.ino Line: ~1640
What: delay(500) at the bottom of loop() means the sleep gate is re-evaluated every 500 ms. In practice the system stays awake ~5–15 s after the GPRS task completes waiting for sync_mode to settle. At 80 mA idle + 3 mA modem-off quiescent = ~2 mAh per wakeup wasted on polling alone across 96 cycles/day = ~190 mAh/day.
